  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">[CA Appeal] KUN - Community/Survivor-Led Shelter &amp; Emergency Response Preparedness &amp; DRR in C.S</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(a) Improve the capacity of the community and local CBO to responsibly manage and utilise their environment and resources as a part of DRR measures in order to maintain sustainable development and emergency preparedness.
(b) Empower local movement by providing support and assistance to the local CBO in developing their own measures to solve humanitarian issues in their village.
(c) Involvement of women, elderlies and PwD where appropriate on leadership, decision making and empowerment.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project site (Kulawi) was affected by the devastating earthquake in Sep 2018. Due to its remote location and frequent flash flooding, there are low infiltration of agencies working in Kulawi. Illegal logging is prevalent and high rainfall makes Kulawi one of the most vulnerable sites for disasters as most recently experienced in Dec 2019.

The programme builds on the resilience and capacities strengthened since the beginning of the Central Sulawesi Response with CA and DEC Appeal funds and linking relief assistance to recovery and enhancing sustainability through community structures. It is an integrated community-managed Eco-DRR that is designed to provide comprehensive DRR actions, recovery, mitigation, preparedness, and response that support the sustainable development. The specific activities integrated in this project are:

(a) Bamboo shelters:
     &#x2022; Training of construction workers.
     &#x2022; Construction.

(b) Emergency preparedness:
     &#x2022; Widerness first aid and psychological first aid training.
     &#x2022; Developing community radio.

(c) SCLR support:
     &#x2022; Empowering  local volunteers by offering micro-grants to initiate Community-Based Organisation (CBO) projects and to support village coordination.</narrative>
  </description>
